    <briefdescription>
<para>Front-end for parsing scalar expressions into GPU/CPU executors. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A <ref refid="classamrex_1_1Parser" kindref="compound">Parser</ref> instance owns the expression string, parser state, and registered variables. After calling <ref refid="classamrex_1_1Parser_1a47d09b414b7b5b8e369c3b58819676fb" kindref="member">define()</ref>, <ref refid="classamrex_1_1Parser_1ac7f2281fb9a99b8c410d9cbc0b20b67b" kindref="member">registerVariables()</ref>, and (optionally) registerUserFn*, the expression can be compiled into a <ref refid="structamrex_1_1ParserExecutor" kindref="compound">ParserExecutor</ref> that evaluates it efficiently on host or device. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
